Title : Portal:Current events/2014 April 29
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|04|29}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]:
**Pro-Russian militants in the [[Eastern Ukraine|eastern Ukrainian]] city of [[Luhansk]] seize the regional administration's headquarters, resulting in a tense standoff with the militants and [[Security Service of Ukraine|security personnel]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27206280 (BBC)]
*[[Syrian Civil War]]:
**At least 37 people are killed and 85 others are injured in multiple explosions in the [[Syria]]n city of [[Homs]].  [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-27203039 (BBC)]

;Business and economy
*The [[United States Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs]] approves three of President [[Barack Obama]]'s nominees to the [[Federal Reserve]], including the nomination of [[Stanley Fischer]] to be its vice chairman. [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/29/us-usa-fed-nominees-idUSBREA3S0N720140429 (Reuters)]

;International relations
*[[Korean maritime border incidents]]:
**[[North Korea]] warns [[South Korea]] that it will conduct live firing near the disputed maritime border. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-27200485# (BBC)]

;Disasters and accidents
*[[Sinking of the MV Sewol|Sinking of the MV ''Sewol'']]:
**Surveillance video footage captures the captain of MV ''Sewol'' Lee Joon-seok escaping the vessel and leaving behind his passengers.  [http://edition.cnn.com/2014/04/27/world/asia/south-korea-ferry-video/index.html?hpt=hp_t1/ (CNN)]
**The [[President of South Korea]] [[Park Geun-hye]] apologises on national television for the government's poor handling of the incident. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-27200542# (BBC)]
**The death toll rises to 205, with 97 passengers still unaccounted for.  [http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/29/world/asia/south-korea-ferry-sinking/index.html?hpt=hp_t2 (CNN)]

;Law and crime
*A shooting at a [[FedEx]] facility in [[Kennesaw, Georgia|Kennesaw]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], United States, leaves six injured with the gunman committing suicide. [http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/29/justice/georgia-fedex/index.html?hpt=hp_t2 (CNN)]
*[[Venezuela]]n officials announce that a former chief of the [[Bolivarian Intelligence Service]], Eliecer Otaiza, was shot and killed on Saturday.  [https://www.bbc.com/news/27202809 (BBC)]
*American prisoner [[Clayton Lockett]] dies of a heart attack in [[Oklahoma]] after a botched execution by [[lethal injection]]. [http://www.aljazeera.com/news/americas/2014/04/oklahoma-prison-botches-inmate-execution-20144300440698611.html (Al Jazeera)]
*[[National Basketball Association|NBA]] [[Commissioner of the NBA|Commissioner]] [[Adam Silver]] announces that [[Los Angeles Clippers]] owner [[Donald Sterling]] is banned from the league for life after a recording of Sterling making racist comments surfaces. Sterling is also fined the maximum allowable US$2.5 million as the NBA examines options for a forced sale. [http://abcnews.go.com/US/nba-donald-sterling-banned-life/story?id=23513899 (ABC News)] [http://www.foxnews.com/sports/2014/04/29/clippers-owner-donald-sterling-banned-for-life-from-nba-fined-25-million-by-nba/ (Fox News)]

